Business Brief -- Grow Group Inc.:
   Profit Posted for Quarter,
   Reversing Prior-Year Loss
The company said the improvement in first-half operating
profit was due to the turnaround in the Consumer 
Professional Products Group, to an operating profit of $1.4
million, compared with an operating loss of $4.5 million a
year earlier, on a 7.6% increase in revenue. The company
added that it expects to see net for the year ending June 30
at the "high end" of its estimated 50 cents and 75 cents a
share.
   In the first half, Grow earned $3.5 million, or 29 cents a
share, compared with a year-earlier loss of $1.5 million, or
13 cents a share. Sales rose 3.5% to $202.4 million from
$195.5 million.